{"type":"message","id":"acdd5c3f","parentId":"e8c05e2a","timestamp":"2026-02-15T09:22:51.860Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 11:22 GMT+2] INVESTIGATE \"SkillsMP\" AND OPENCLAW SKILLS ECOSYSTEM.\n\n1.  **Identity Check:** Search for \"SkillsMP AI skills marketplace\".\n    *   *CRITICAL:* If \"SkillsMP\" does not exist or appears to be a hallucination/typo, switch focus to **ClawHub** (https://clawhub.com), which is the official OpenClaw skill registry mentioned in our docs.\n    *   *Context:* The user might be using a placeholder name. Treat ClawHub as the target if SkillsMP is missing.\n\n2.  **Skill Scout:** Search (via ClawHub or general web search for \"OpenClaw skills\") for existing skills matching:\n    *   **DMarket/Steam:** Trading, inventory management.\n    *   **Redis:** Database inspection, Redis 8 support.\n    *   **Python:** Debugging, linting, \"python-expert\".\n    *   **Market Analysis:** Price tracking, crypto/skin market tools.\n\n3.  **Auth Check:**\n    *   Does the `openclaw skills` CLI or ClawHub require an API key?\n    *   Are there benefits to having an account (private skills, higher rate limits)?\n\n4.  **Comparison Table:**\n    *   Create a table of the top 3-5 candidates found.\n    *   Columns: Skill Name, Popularity (Stars/Downloads), Security (Verified?), Compatibility (SACS-2026/Vertex?).\n\n5.  **Verdict:**\n    *   Should we integrate this registry?\n    *   Do we need a key?"}],"timestamp":1771147371858}}
