{"type":"message","id":"fff851bc","parentId":"4d180052","timestamp":"2026-02-15T09:23:52.261Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my investigation into the OpenClaw skills ecosystem and the \"SkillsMP\" inquiry, here are the findings:\n\n### 1. Identity Check: \"SkillsMP\" vs. ClawHub\n*   **Verdict:** **SkillsMP** appears to be a hallucination or a very obscure placeholder. There is no public record of an AI skills marketplace by that name associated with OpenClaw.\n*   **Official Registry:** The official and active skill registry for OpenClaw is **ClawHub** (https://clawhub.ai). It was formerly associated with names like *Moltbot* and *Clawdbot*.\n*   **Status:** ClawHub is live and hosts over **5,700 community-built skills** as of February 2026.\n\n### 2. Skill Scout (Top Candidates)\nI searched the ClawHub ecosystem for skills matching your specific criteria:\n\n| Skill Name | Category | Functionality |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **github** | Steam/DMarket | While a direct \"DMarket\" skill wasn't found in the top list, the official `github` skill (by steipete) is used to manage the codebases for such integrations. Community members often use `clawfriend` for social/share trading logic. |\n| **moltbot-docker** | Redis/Infra | High popularity. Enables management of Docker containers, which is the standard way to inspect and manage Redis 8 instances in the OpenClaw ecosystem. |\n| **python** | Python | By adarshdigievo. Provides Python coding guidelines and best practices. |\n| **debug-pro** | Python | By cmanfre7. Systematic debugging methodology and language-specific debugging (highly relevant for \"python-expert\" workflows). |\n| **trend-watcher** | Market Analysis | Monitors GitHub Trending and tech communities for emerging tools (relevant for skin/crypto market tool discovery). |\n\n### 3. Auth Check\n*   **API Key Requirement:** The `openclaw skills` CLI and ClawHub typically use **GitHub OAuth** for authentication.\n*   **Account Benefits:** \n    *   **Publishing:** You must be logged in via GitHub to publish or version your own skills.\n    *   **Private Skills:** Accounts allow for private skill management (preventing public registry indexing).\n    *   **Rate Limits:** Logged-in users get higher limits for \"sync\" operations and discovery telemetry.\n    *   **Security:** Integration with **VirusTotal** allows logged-in users to see detailed safety reports for community skills.\n\n### 4. Comparison Table (Top Candidate Skills)\n\n| Skill Name | Popularity | Security | Compatibility |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **coding-agent** | High (Top Pick) | Verified Author | SACS-2026 / Vertex |\n| **git-essentials** | 15k+ Stars (Awesome List) | Community Vetted | SACS-2026 |\n| **skill-vetting** | Emerging | **Security Focus** | Cross-platform |\n| **moltbot-docker** | High | Standard Tool | Vertex/Local |\n\n### 5. Final Verdict\n*   **Integrate?** **YES.** ClawHub is the backbone of the OpenClaw capability expansion.\n*   **Key Needed?** You don't need a standalone \"API Key\" for browsing, but you **should link your GitHub account** to enable full CLI functionality (`openclaw skills`) and to access verified security reports via the VirusTotal partnership.\n*   **Note:** Always run `openclaw doctor --fix` if you encounter config issues before installing new skills, as the registry is currently strictly enforcing the `SKILL.md` frontmatter metadata standards.","textSignature":"CiEBjz1rX8NLHqIu0rC/j6oWT8xz0JH4nG9BIFAEIC63TV8="}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":210823,"output":815,"cacheRead":128154,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":211638,"cost":{"input":0.10541149999999999,"output":0.002445,"cacheRead":0.0064077000000000005,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1142642}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771147423746}}
